UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Alvin O. MONSON, Appellee. No. 8237. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 3, 1936. J. Charles Dennis, U. S. Atty., F. A. Pellegrini, Asst. U. S. Atty., and George R. Stuntz, Atty., Department of Justice, all of Seattle, Wash., and Julius C. Martin, Director, Bureau of War Risk Litigation, of Washington, D. C., for the United States. Tyre H. Hollander and George E. Flood, both of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
